  "why": "The paper reports and analyzes statistical failure patterns (per-model ASR/EASR, JQN, query/token cost) and performs ablations on seed-selection and mutator choices that explain which testing factors increase or decrease jailbreak success. These analyses provide partial diagnostic insight (i.e., which prompt-generation strategies and which models are more/less vulnerable). However, the paper does not link discovered failures to underlying model vulnerabilities (e.g., reliance on spurious/non-robust features, dataset bias, or internal neuron/activation patterns) or provide causal attribution beyond high-level hypotheses. Hence it meets the 'Medium' level: statistical and internal-fuzzer diagnostic insight but not root-cause explanations of model weaknesses.",
